    &lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;
        Next, we need to create a function that we can call to render the mustache templates. You can refactor this code and put it on a separate class so you can call it accross all your controllers. I'm just putting it here for demonstration purposes.
        <div class='bogus-wrapper'><notextile><figure class='code'><figcaption><span>"Compile Mustache Function" </span><a href='https://github.com/edvinasbartkus/grails-mustache'>"Thanks to edvinasbartkus" </a></figcaption> <div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
