</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'><span class="o">&lt;</span><span class="n">pre</span><span class="o">&gt;&lt;</span><span class="n">code</span><span class="o">&gt;</span>
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></notextile></div>

        This function accepts a model object which Mustache will use to render (I'll explain it further when we get to the Mustache codes) and a Reader object that holds the Mustache templates to be rendered. This function basically dumps the output of the MustacheBuilder to a ByteArrayOutputStream which we can then return as string via the .toString() function. For more information on the MustacheBuilder, please visit their home page at &lt;a href="https://github.com/spullara/mustache.java"&gt;https://github.com/spullara/mustache.java&lt;/a&gt;
